WEBVTT

00:02.089 --> 00:03.438
[CRACKLING]

00:03.612 --> 00:05.483
WOLF:
Previously onFuture Man:

00:05.657 --> 00:07.920
WOMAN:
These three have stolen
a time travel device.

00:08.095 --> 00:10.140
They can be anytime, anywhere.

00:10.314 --> 00:11.446
I got a ping.
Someone just invented

00:11.620 --> 00:13.491
sliced bread
700 years too early.

00:13.665 --> 00:16.364
Wolf-Hart just decapitated
Shoji the Honorable,

00:16.538 --> 00:19.671
wiping out an entire line
of noble warriors.

00:19.845 --> 00:21.847
Da, da!

00:22.022 --> 00:24.111
TOCH:
Check out this book.
It's got to be Wolf-Hart.

00:24.285 --> 00:26.069
He set her humanity aflame.

00:26.243 --> 00:27.462
They're hiding in Russia.

00:27.636 --> 00:28.985
Two timelines
just momentarily merged.

00:29.159 --> 00:30.421
I think we're looking
at temporal decay.

00:30.595 --> 00:32.423
Future and past
existing simultaneously,

00:32.597 --> 00:33.816
space-time collapsing
in on itself.

00:33.990 --> 00:35.122
Are you there, God?

00:35.296 --> 00:36.862
VOICE:
Don't call me that.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.256
What should I call you?VOICE: How about "friend?"

00:39.430 --> 00:40.953
You must come to me.

00:41.128 --> 00:42.825
I will give you
the coordinates to find me.

00:42.999 --> 00:45.045
Hey, give me that.No, I got it!

00:45.219 --> 00:46.524
I'm taking us somewhere safe.

00:46.698 --> 00:48.048
[♪♪♪]

00:56.143 --> 00:58.449
[♪♪♪]

01:15.118 --> 01:17.033
[♪♪♪]

01:43.190 --> 01:44.756
Huh?

02:10.826 --> 02:12.044
[ALL SHOUT ANGRILY]

02:12.219 --> 02:13.611
What's going on?

02:13.785 --> 02:17.528
You piss yourself in moments
half as tense as that.

02:17.702 --> 02:20.749
I had faith,
and my faith was rewarded.

02:20.923 --> 02:22.968
My destiny is not back there.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.057
[WARRIORS SHOUTING]

02:26.842 --> 02:28.191
It's up there.

02:31.063 --> 02:33.283
VOICE:
Yes, Josh. You are close.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.807
What's on top
of the mountain?

02:35.981 --> 02:38.723
[SIGHS]
Home.

02:38.897 --> 02:40.725
We're off to see
the all-knowing,

02:40.899 --> 02:43.685
benevolent, the great,
the powerful--

02:43.859 --> 02:45.687
[SCREAMING]

02:47.950 --> 02:49.821
[♪♪♪]

02:58.700 --> 03:00.571
[GRUNTING]

03:07.883 --> 03:09.754
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

03:18.198 --> 03:19.677
[GRUNTING]

03:19.851 --> 03:21.418
[YELLS]

03:21.592 --> 03:23.594
[CRYING]

03:26.467 --> 03:28.817
VOICE:
Josh, my friend,
I have been patient.

03:28.991 --> 03:31.341
I have waited
for your scratch to heal.

03:31.515 --> 03:33.343
It's not a scratch.

03:33.517 --> 03:35.432
Okay, the scent
of my leg repels animals.

03:35.606 --> 03:37.782
Except for vultures,
who just keep following me.

03:37.956 --> 03:40.524
VOICE:
Today,
you must climb the mountain.

03:40.698 --> 03:42.657
[STAMMERS]
I can barely walk.

03:42.831 --> 03:45.355
You keep pushing me to climb,
and every time that I do,

03:45.529 --> 03:49.098
the wound just opens up again,
and it's making it worse.

03:49.272 --> 03:51.405
Why can't you just
come meet me here?

03:51.579 --> 03:53.015
VOICE:
The mountain
will not come to you,

03:53.189 --> 03:54.973
you must come to the mountain.

03:55.147 --> 03:57.367
Don't give up,
not when you are so close.

03:57.541 --> 03:58.760
Exactly, exactly.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.588
Doesn't close count
for anything?

04:01.763 --> 04:04.244
Look, I just want to go home.

04:04.418 --> 04:06.507
I thought we were friends.

04:06.681 --> 04:08.465
It turns out
I'm just that sad Bible guy

04:08.639 --> 04:10.511
who God keeps testing
over and over again.

04:10.685 --> 04:11.642
You know the one.

04:11.816 --> 04:13.949
VOICE:
Uh...Jesus?

04:14.123 --> 04:16.430
No! Job.

04:16.604 --> 04:17.605
Right?

04:17.779 --> 04:19.824
VOICE:
Hm. If you say so.

04:21.870 --> 04:24.568
[JOSH PANTING]

04:29.312 --> 04:31.662
Oh. What took you so long?

04:31.836 --> 04:34.796
Oh, you know, I just kept
falling and crying.

04:34.970 --> 04:36.624
Mm-hmm.

04:36.798 --> 04:38.016
Oh, yeah.

04:39.540 --> 04:41.063
Goddamn it.

04:41.237 --> 04:43.674
I asked for King Boletes.
these are Death Caps.

04:43.848 --> 04:45.763
Wanna guess what happens
if you eat these?

04:45.937 --> 04:48.375
This is fine dining,
not college improv.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.899
I'm sorry, okay?
I'm doing my best.

04:51.073 --> 04:53.771
Just cut me some slack.
I'm going to my room.

04:53.945 --> 04:56.121
[MUMBLING]
No appreciation...

04:56.296 --> 04:58.602
Oh, well,
if it isn't little Miss

04:58.776 --> 05:00.300
"Haven't Been Home
in Three Days."

05:00.474 --> 05:02.214
[GROANS]

05:04.478 --> 05:07.742
Oh, yeah,
my chin is a-barkin'.

05:07.916 --> 05:09.570
No one's making you
wear that thing.

05:09.744 --> 05:11.920
Yeah, well, I'm sick
of killing would-be rapers.

05:12.094 --> 05:13.965
Hey, boy? Boy?What?

05:14.139 --> 05:15.837
Why'd you bring us
to yet another time

05:16.011 --> 05:17.360
where women are treated
like garbage?

05:17.534 --> 05:20.798
I'm so sorry.
It's called "all of history."

05:20.972 --> 05:22.278
What do you want me
to do about it?

05:22.452 --> 05:24.019
[GROANS]

05:25.716 --> 05:27.370
Those are bear traps.

05:27.544 --> 05:29.241
And they need a-mendin'.

05:29.416 --> 05:30.808
Rabbit's 10 away.

05:30.982 --> 05:32.854
I made sous-vide bags
out of elk bladders.

05:33.028 --> 05:34.551
It locks in the flavor.

05:34.725 --> 05:36.031
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
it's food.

05:36.205 --> 05:38.860
Who gives a shit?Ooh, careful.

05:39.034 --> 05:40.340
[GROANS]

05:42.385 --> 05:46.084
Okay, so how was your day?

05:46.258 --> 05:49.174
Well, I beat my PR
on beaver pelts.

05:49.349 --> 05:51.438
97.Oh, wow.

05:51.612 --> 05:54.179
Yeah, pretty good
considering those Mohawk dicks

05:54.354 --> 05:55.833
are messing with my traps.

05:56.007 --> 05:58.183
Oh, well,
you know, if you like,

05:58.358 --> 06:00.098
I can speak with the Mohawk.

06:00.272 --> 06:03.406
They're allied with the French,
and they don't take too kindly

06:03.580 --> 06:06.148
to independent operators
moving in on their territory,

06:06.322 --> 06:08.933
but if I were to communicate
our neutrality--

06:09.107 --> 06:10.631
You know what?And then we can--

06:10.805 --> 06:13.373
Stop you right there
Mr. "Tell Morning Not to Come."

06:13.547 --> 06:15.766
I gave you no cause
to retrieve the book.

06:15.940 --> 06:18.595
TIGER:
Boy. Read it.

06:18.769 --> 06:19.944
JOSH:
Do I have to?

06:20.118 --> 06:21.293
TIGER:
Read the passage.

06:22.643 --> 06:24.645
JOSH:
"Climax upon climax.

06:24.819 --> 06:27.735
A cascade that had
no beginning and no end.

06:27.909 --> 06:30.259
I knew I must tell the world
what happened

06:30.433 --> 06:33.044
between those
beet-stained sheets."

06:33.218 --> 06:34.655
I mean, you could've just--
Pbbt.

06:34.829 --> 06:36.657
finger-blasted her,
called it a day.

06:36.831 --> 06:39.529
But no, you had to
go ahead and inspire

06:39.703 --> 06:42.314
a whole new genre
of literary erotic fiction.

06:42.489 --> 06:45.143
I only do things one way,
and that's all the way.

06:45.317 --> 06:47.494
And that is why
you are on a soft lockdown

06:47.668 --> 06:49.409
till further notice, soldier.

06:49.583 --> 06:50.932
I like it here.

06:51.106 --> 06:53.195
The air is clear,
the killin's good.

06:53.369 --> 06:55.066
And I don't need you
messing it up

06:55.240 --> 06:57.286
by putting your
stupid mark on history again.

06:57.460 --> 06:58.722
You're treating me
like a goddamn Josh.

06:58.896 --> 06:59.941
JOSH:
Hey.

07:00.115 --> 07:01.551
Don't act like
such a prisoner.

07:01.725 --> 07:03.423
You go to the trading post
and sell my furs.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.076
Yeah, once a week.

07:05.250 --> 07:07.035
You're running around
free doing whatever you like

07:07.209 --> 07:09.341
while I'm stuck here
changing the Josh's bandages.

07:09.516 --> 07:10.952
I change them too.Once.

07:11.126 --> 07:12.432
Half-way through,
you gave up,

07:12.606 --> 07:14.085
and you handed them to me.

07:14.259 --> 07:15.696
JOSH:
Hey, Tiger.

07:17.654 --> 07:19.787
The Mohawk did not
destroy your traps.

07:19.961 --> 07:22.659
There's no human
that can bend iron like this.

07:24.052 --> 07:25.532
Whitey.

07:25.706 --> 07:28.448
Oh, Lord.
Not this again.

07:30.188 --> 07:32.887
Albino bear of legend.

07:33.061 --> 07:36.107
Ten feet tall,
snow-white fur.

07:36.281 --> 07:40.808
Eyes as red as the devil.
Heart as black as...

07:40.982 --> 07:41.939
also the devil.

07:42.113 --> 07:43.985
Whitey is a myth.

07:44.159 --> 07:46.204
Tall tale told by trappers
to scare each other

07:46.378 --> 07:47.423
around the campfire.

07:47.597 --> 07:49.077
No, he is real,

07:49.251 --> 07:51.558
and if I do nothing else
on this Earth,

07:51.732 --> 07:53.385
I will kill Whitey.

07:53.560 --> 07:55.475
[♪♪♪]

07:58.303 --> 08:00.523
Hunter's log, day 187.

08:00.697 --> 08:02.307
Having thinned
the beaver population

08:02.482 --> 08:03.874
to near extinction levels,

08:04.048 --> 08:06.224
I direct my gaze
to more elusive quarry.

08:06.398 --> 08:08.662
In nature, there can only be
one apex predator.

08:08.836 --> 08:10.577
My mission?

08:10.751 --> 08:12.927
To kill my way to the very
top of this food chain.

08:13.101 --> 08:15.538
Failure is not an option.

08:15.712 --> 08:18.454
I rely on keen instinct,
finely-honed skills,

08:18.628 --> 08:21.065
and whatever savagery
this hunt requires.

08:21.239 --> 08:24.199
Ursine maggot.

08:24.373 --> 08:26.723
Hmm.

08:26.897 --> 08:28.725
Clue...

08:30.422 --> 08:32.033
and a snack.

08:37.560 --> 08:40.345
Female.
In heat.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.957
Same here, sister.

08:44.785 --> 08:46.787
There she is.

08:49.877 --> 08:52.880
Five minutes.
Maybe 10.

08:53.054 --> 08:55.926
Looks like a bear
does shit in the woods.

09:03.543 --> 09:06.720
Ah. We are having
reindeer sweetbreads,

09:06.894 --> 09:08.025
wild asparagus,

09:08.199 --> 09:10.288
a salad of chickweed,
peppergrass--

09:10.462 --> 09:13.683
Hunting. Need protein.

09:17.818 --> 09:20.168
That's it.
I can't live like this.

09:20.342 --> 09:22.605
[MUMBLES]

09:25.477 --> 09:28.306
[YELLS]

09:33.703 --> 09:35.487
I just need to feel seen.

09:35.662 --> 09:37.011
Yeah, well, buy a mirror.

09:37.185 --> 09:38.447
[GASPS]

09:38.621 --> 09:40.971
[JOSH PANTING]

09:41.145 --> 09:43.147
Oh, God, the stench.

09:43.321 --> 09:46.673
JOSH:
It's-it's bad today.

09:46.847 --> 09:50.198
All right, someone needs
to change the Josh.

09:56.117 --> 09:58.815
Fine. I'll do it.

10:03.254 --> 10:05.169
[EXHALES]

10:07.650 --> 10:11.132
All right,
let's have a look at this.

10:13.569 --> 10:16.616
Oh, yowzer me.
Yikes.

10:16.790 --> 10:18.530
I am not liking
the color of that ooze.

10:18.705 --> 10:19.967
You know, it's like chicken.

10:20.141 --> 10:22.099
You want the juices
to run clear.

10:22.273 --> 10:24.014
Yep, well,
it's about that time.

10:24.188 --> 10:26.408
No, no!
No one is cutting my leg off.

10:26.582 --> 10:28.323
Yeah,
to get through that femur,

10:28.497 --> 10:30.281
I'm definitely
gonna have to saw.

10:30.455 --> 10:31.674
No, no sawing, either.

10:31.848 --> 10:33.937
I heard tale
of a medicine woman

10:34.111 --> 10:35.983
at the trading post
who works wonders.

10:36.157 --> 10:37.375
I bet I could
get you in to see her.

10:37.549 --> 10:39.551
No, no medicine woman.

10:39.726 --> 10:41.510
Okay, my leg is going to heal.

10:41.684 --> 10:42.990
Okay, I know it will.

10:43.164 --> 10:44.861
Why would somebody put me
through this

10:45.035 --> 10:46.428
if I can't overcome it?

10:46.602 --> 10:48.343
Pretty shitty thing
for a friend to do.

10:48.517 --> 10:49.953
VOICE:
I'm shitty? You're shitty!

10:50.127 --> 10:51.563
Uh--

10:54.741 --> 10:55.742
Okay, buddy.

10:55.916 --> 10:57.657
[SNORING]

10:57.831 --> 10:59.484
[METALLIC SCRAPE]

10:59.659 --> 11:01.661
TIGER:
Hold him steady.
He'll be a-thrashin'.

11:04.315 --> 11:05.665
No, no,
please, please, please!

11:05.839 --> 11:07.231
Don't cut my leg off, please.

11:07.405 --> 11:09.277
I swear I will go see
the medicine woman.

11:09.451 --> 11:11.758
See what happens when you set
some firm boundaries?

11:11.932 --> 11:14.543
Don't even start.You coddle him.

11:16.719 --> 11:19.200
JOSH:
So what does this
medicine woman do?

11:19.374 --> 11:21.202
WOLF:
More like
what doesn't she do?

11:21.376 --> 11:23.334
She's a therapist,
frontier doctor,

11:23.508 --> 11:25.293
weight-loss guru.

11:25.467 --> 11:27.295
She helped me drop
the Frontier Fifteen,

11:27.469 --> 11:30.385
and cured
my seasonal affective disorder.

11:30.559 --> 11:33.257
Turns out,
it's okay to be sad.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.477
Good. I thought it was like
a religious thing.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.914
Religion? Hell no.

11:38.088 --> 11:40.264
Yeah, yeah, I know.
You and Tiger don't believe.

11:40.438 --> 11:41.788
How could we?

11:41.962 --> 11:43.746
Growing up in the sewer
with the Biotics

11:43.920 --> 11:46.357
sending down
those toddler bombs.

11:46.531 --> 11:48.446
I'm sorry, the what bombs?

11:48.620 --> 11:50.318
I've told you
about the toddler bombs.

11:50.492 --> 11:52.146
Human children
genetically engineered

11:52.320 --> 11:53.582
to blow up when you hug them.

11:53.756 --> 11:55.279
No. That's fucked up.

11:55.453 --> 11:56.846
WOLF:
That's not the fucked up part.

11:57.020 --> 11:58.805
We could always spot
the toddler bombs

11:58.979 --> 12:02.025
because any actual sewer child
was far too emotionally damaged

12:02.199 --> 12:03.810
to yearn
for physical affection.

12:03.984 --> 12:05.072
JOSH:
Holy shit.

12:05.246 --> 12:06.421
Again,
not the fucked up part.

12:06.595 --> 12:08.205
How is that not
the fucked up part?

12:08.379 --> 12:12.427
Eventually,
us older kids captured the TBs

12:12.601 --> 12:15.169
and forced them to perform
for us in a makeshift circus.

12:15.343 --> 12:18.041
Okay,
just cut to the fucked up part.

12:20.696 --> 12:23.960
We laughed at one
of the toddler bombs' poetry.

12:24.134 --> 12:26.006
It was bad.

12:26.180 --> 12:27.877
He had the mind
of a three-year-old.

12:29.357 --> 12:31.011
But we didn't have to laugh.

12:32.839 --> 12:35.319
He took it pretty hard,

12:35.493 --> 12:39.149
ended up hugging himself
and self-detonating.

12:39.323 --> 12:41.630
All the other TBs
realized that they, too,

12:41.804 --> 12:43.719
were just there
for our amusement.

12:43.893 --> 12:45.634
[SIGHS]
Yeah.

12:45.808 --> 12:50.682
Pop, pop, pop, pop.

12:52.684 --> 12:54.817
Mass toddler suicide.

12:57.515 --> 13:00.214
That's when I realized
there was no God.

13:00.388 --> 13:02.694
He was just some sky genie
people made up

13:02.869 --> 13:03.913
to give them hope.

13:04.087 --> 13:05.567
[HORSE WHINNIES]

13:07.830 --> 13:10.354
[♪♪♪]

13:20.234 --> 13:21.801
You doubled back.

13:23.324 --> 13:24.716
Why?

13:27.328 --> 13:28.459
Why here?

13:30.244 --> 13:31.462
So visible.

13:32.681 --> 13:34.596
So exposed.

13:36.903 --> 13:38.948
The fuck were you looking for?

13:44.388 --> 13:46.477
[GASPS]
Oh.

13:46.651 --> 13:49.002
[LAUGHS]
Is this bear something,

13:49.176 --> 13:50.960
or is this bear something?

13:53.397 --> 13:54.921
You're looking at me.

13:55.095 --> 13:57.184
[BEAR GROWLING]Okay.

13:57.358 --> 13:58.533
Okay.

13:58.707 --> 14:01.492
You want to dance? Huh?

14:01.666 --> 14:03.755
You want to dance?

14:03.930 --> 14:06.019
Let's fucking Lindy Hop.

14:09.805 --> 14:12.068
The old trading post.

14:12.242 --> 14:15.942
Burned to the ground
by the outlaw Wild Sam Bladden.

14:16.116 --> 14:18.205
Folks here
are gonna have the last laugh.

14:18.379 --> 14:21.338
We're rebuilding this
trading center to be stronger,

14:21.512 --> 14:22.731
more vibrant than ever.

14:22.905 --> 14:25.081
Wait, did you say "we?"

14:25.255 --> 14:28.215
[IN MOHAWK]
We've prepared 150 bowls
of salmon velouté.

14:28.389 --> 14:30.130
JOSH:
What's happening?

14:30.304 --> 14:33.002
WOLF [IN MOHAWK]:
Prepare 50 more.

14:33.176 --> 14:35.222
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

14:35.396 --> 14:37.833
JOSH:
How do you know
all these people?

14:38.007 --> 14:41.358
Wolf, did you build a thriving
international hub of commerce?

14:41.532 --> 14:43.317
No.

14:43.491 --> 14:45.014
I served
in a consulting capacity.

14:45.188 --> 14:47.060
Nothing formal.
I'm nobody here.

14:47.234 --> 14:49.889
[SPEAKING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]

14:50.063 --> 14:51.891
Just go on.

14:52.065 --> 14:53.936
He's just confused.

14:54.110 --> 14:57.679
Trust me, around here,
I'm a ghost, a shadow.

14:57.853 --> 14:59.594
My name's on nothing.

15:02.423 --> 15:04.686
Your brand is.

15:04.860 --> 15:06.688
Goddamn it, Wolf.

15:08.168 --> 15:09.604
Wolves were sacred
to the Mohawk

15:09.778 --> 15:12.041
long before I got here.

15:12.215 --> 15:15.305
I just need to talk to Acona
about the new inventory.

15:15.479 --> 15:17.394
Fall is all about beavers.

15:19.875 --> 15:22.138
You're doing it again.
You're gonna get us caught.

15:22.312 --> 15:24.097
[IN MOHAWK]
Any update?

15:24.271 --> 15:26.273
[IN MOHAWK]
The Vikings are in!

15:26.447 --> 15:28.362
Great work!

15:31.452 --> 15:33.106
Wolf, you promised--

15:33.280 --> 15:35.282
[IN ENGLISH]
I'm gonna stop you right there.

15:35.456 --> 15:37.632
Selling fur is all about
building relationships,

15:37.806 --> 15:39.373
So, yes,
when I come to the post,

15:39.547 --> 15:41.114
I kibitz a bit.

15:41.288 --> 15:43.072
As Lew Wasserman said:

15:43.246 --> 15:44.421
"Every conversation

15:44.595 --> 15:46.510
is a business meeting
in disguise."

15:46.684 --> 15:48.469
But don't you worry about me.

15:48.643 --> 15:51.254
I learned my lesson with Dasha.

15:51.428 --> 15:55.041
That's why I've only
been taking illiterate lovers.

15:55.215 --> 15:58.435
Wolf, that was not the lesson,
and you know it.

15:58.609 --> 16:00.133
Shall we go see
the medicine woman?

16:00.307 --> 16:01.830
Okay.

16:02.004 --> 16:03.527
Don't push me.
Don't push me.

16:10.447 --> 16:13.668
[SPEAKING IN MOHAWK]

16:13.842 --> 16:17.628
[TRANSLATING]
She says it's not your leg
that's the source of your pain.

16:17.802 --> 16:20.457
[LAUGHS]
Of course it is.
What else would it be?

16:20.631 --> 16:22.242
[MEDICINE WOMAN
SPEAKING IN MOHAWK]

16:24.809 --> 16:26.942
A spiritual crisis.

16:27.116 --> 16:30.250
What? That's ridiculous.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.559
What would be the nature
of that crisis,

16:35.733 --> 16:37.822
in her opinion?

16:41.696 --> 16:46.918
[IN MOHAWK]
Heal your mind,
your body will follow.

16:47.093 --> 16:49.617
Did she just say
something profound?

16:50.531 --> 16:52.054
She always does.

16:53.447 --> 16:54.404
Speak freely.

16:56.145 --> 16:58.495
This is a judgment-free yurt.

17:02.717 --> 17:05.328
I've been talking with God
for the last eight months.

17:07.243 --> 17:11.117
He lives inside my ear,
and he tells me what to do.

17:11.291 --> 17:12.683
We're, like,
super, super close.

17:12.857 --> 17:14.990
He even has me call him friend.

17:15.164 --> 17:16.905
But right now,
we're in, like, a fight,

17:17.079 --> 17:18.733
and I don't know
what to make of it anymore.

17:18.907 --> 17:20.604
I'm starting to think
it's all in my head,

17:20.778 --> 17:22.084
and I'm just going crazy.

17:22.258 --> 17:23.781
VOICE:  Josh, do not go down this road.

17:23.955 --> 17:25.783
Remember the Miracle
of the Goo?

17:25.957 --> 17:28.699
Goo? It was a knob.

17:28.873 --> 17:30.527
Okay,
I found a knob with my hand,

17:30.701 --> 17:32.268
something I could've done
on my own.

17:32.442 --> 17:33.791
I'm not an idiot.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.666
Sorry.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.016
It's okay.

17:41.190 --> 17:44.498
What's...
tiny ear God saying now?

17:44.672 --> 17:47.109
He's telling me
that he's real.

17:47.283 --> 17:50.112
But what kind of God knows
less about the Bible than me?

17:50.286 --> 17:52.288
I mean, isn't he
supposed to be omniscient?

17:52.462 --> 17:54.682
What kind of God would let my
leg get caught in a bear trap?

17:54.856 --> 17:56.336
VOICE:
That's so on you, bro.

17:56.510 --> 17:57.859
[SCOFFS]

18:01.906 --> 18:04.257
WOLF:
Whoa, it's happening.

18:04.431 --> 18:06.128
Don't fight it, Josh.

18:06.302 --> 18:07.303
[♪♪♪]

18:07.477 --> 18:09.218
Let her in.

18:17.792 --> 18:20.447
She's right.

18:20.621 --> 18:21.926
I don't believe in myself.

18:22.101 --> 18:24.538
I am a salmon
swimming against a tide

18:24.712 --> 18:26.714
of my own self-doubt.

18:26.888 --> 18:29.673
I created a sky genie
just to give me hope.

18:29.847 --> 18:32.807
VOICE:
Josh, don't abandon me
when we are this close.

18:32.981 --> 18:35.810
You know what, bro?

18:35.984 --> 18:37.464
I'm done.

18:38.987 --> 18:41.337
I release you.

18:41.511 --> 18:43.209
VOICE:
You release me?

18:43.383 --> 18:45.515
You know what?
Fine, be that way.

18:45.689 --> 18:46.995
[FOOTSTEPS STOMPING]

18:47.169 --> 18:48.518
[DOOR SLAMMING]

18:48.692 --> 18:51.130
A real God
wouldn't have to slam a door.

18:54.263 --> 18:55.134
Hello?

18:58.572 --> 19:00.095
He's gone.

19:00.269 --> 19:01.488
I'm free.

19:01.662 --> 19:04.317
[LAUGHS]

19:04.491 --> 19:06.797
[EXHALES]

19:06.971 --> 19:09.104
[SPEAKING IN MOHAWK]

19:09.278 --> 19:10.758
She's asking
if we want to stay

19:10.932 --> 19:13.282
for a shave and a sweat lodge.

19:13.456 --> 19:15.066
Tuesdays are pretty slow
around here.

19:15.241 --> 19:18.113
Oh. Yeah, that sounds great.

19:21.334 --> 19:22.639
I feel lighter.

19:22.813 --> 19:24.206
WOLF:
Well, you are lighter.

19:24.380 --> 19:26.208
I usually drop
three to four LBs

19:26.382 --> 19:28.123
of a liquid stress
after a good schvitz.

19:28.297 --> 19:29.951
[LAUGHS]
Yeah.

19:30.125 --> 19:31.996
You know what?
It was just nice to talk

19:32.171 --> 19:34.085
to somebody
who was actually there.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.784
Well, now that you realize
you're never going home,

19:36.958 --> 19:39.221
you can focus on being happy
in the here and now.

19:39.395 --> 19:41.658
I wouldn't say "never."
You know, never say never.

19:41.832 --> 19:42.790
Normally, I'd agree,

19:42.964 --> 19:44.618
except in this case.

19:44.792 --> 19:47.490
We are history's
most wanted fugitives.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.753
A couple of five-Os
are definitely stationed

19:49.927 --> 19:52.408
outside of every Futturman
household in the universe.

19:52.582 --> 19:55.542
Did tiny ear God give
you a plan to get past them?

19:55.716 --> 19:57.457
No.

19:57.631 --> 20:00.155
I guess he was more of, like,
a big picture sort of God.

20:00.329 --> 20:02.940
Yet another reason
you should've called bullshit.

20:03.114 --> 20:04.420
God is in the details.

20:04.594 --> 20:08.424
Huh.
Yeah, I mean, I guess that...

20:08.598 --> 20:10.209
every other Futturman house

20:10.383 --> 20:11.819
would have another
version of me.

20:11.993 --> 20:13.516
Who you'd have to kill
to take their place,

20:13.690 --> 20:16.084
and that's
the best-case scenario.

20:16.258 --> 20:19.261
No, more likely, time
constables kill your parents,

20:19.435 --> 20:21.829
turn them into cyborgs,
and use them to torture you.

20:22.003 --> 20:24.614
So in that version
you technically could go home,

20:24.788 --> 20:26.486
but your robot parents
would kill you.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.531
Is that what you want, Josh?

20:28.705 --> 20:31.578
Your robot parents to kill you?

20:31.752 --> 20:33.362
No.

20:35.712 --> 20:37.845
Wait.

20:38.019 --> 20:40.195
I've just had an idea
that'll change everything.

20:40.369 --> 20:41.327
What? Tell me.

20:41.501 --> 20:43.329
Vegan carnitas.

20:44.243 --> 20:46.201
[GRUNTS]

20:48.159 --> 20:49.857
These are King Boletes.

20:50.031 --> 20:51.380
They have the perfect density

20:51.554 --> 20:55.166
to make faux-Mex
taste like "Fuck yes."

20:55.341 --> 20:57.647
So to sum up,
you're never going home,

20:57.821 --> 21:00.998
your God is dead,
and taco Tuesday is on.

21:01.172 --> 21:03.697
[♪♪♪]

21:08.092 --> 21:10.399
Whitey, Whitey, Whitey.

21:10.573 --> 21:14.316
[CHUCKLES]
Looks like someone's not smarter
than the average bear,

21:14.490 --> 21:16.927
because you just wandered
into a sea

21:17.101 --> 21:19.234
of my very best...

21:20.844 --> 21:21.932
traps?

21:25.153 --> 21:27.416
[CHIMES TINKLING]

21:32.552 --> 21:36.033
[♪♪♪]

21:36.207 --> 21:37.557
[BEAR GROWLING]

21:37.731 --> 21:39.559
[SCREAMS]

21:43.954 --> 21:46.435
[WOLF HOWLS IN DISTANCE]

21:51.745 --> 21:54.008
Looks like Tiger's gonna be
a little late.

21:54.182 --> 21:55.488
Just go ahead and start.

21:55.662 --> 21:56.880
Not hungry.

21:57.054 --> 22:00.231
These King Bs
marinated for hours.

22:00.406 --> 22:03.365
They bleed like real meat.

22:03.539 --> 22:05.193
Just...

22:05.367 --> 22:06.542
take a bite.

22:06.716 --> 22:08.239
I don't want to.No, just try it.

22:08.414 --> 22:09.589
I don't want to.No, just--

22:09.763 --> 22:11.286
Stop it!

22:11.460 --> 22:13.201
Just stop pretending
we're family.

22:13.375 --> 22:15.334
I could not be farther away
from my family.

22:15.508 --> 22:16.639
Tiger gets it.

22:16.813 --> 22:17.858
She knows
we're just three people

22:18.032 --> 22:19.512
going insane
in the wilderness.

22:19.686 --> 22:22.776
Our only future is running,
and I can't even stand up.

22:22.950 --> 22:26.345
So just leave me alone.

22:29.826 --> 22:30.784
What are you doing?

22:30.958 --> 22:32.742
Going out.Where?

22:32.916 --> 22:35.266
Do you know
what I've sacrificed

22:35.441 --> 22:36.659
to support the two of you?

22:36.833 --> 22:39.880
The dreams I've put on hold?

22:40.054 --> 22:41.621
Tell Tiger...

22:41.795 --> 22:43.579
I went out to buy a mirror.

22:43.753 --> 22:45.015
What?

22:45.189 --> 22:47.278
It relates
to an earlier conversation

22:47.453 --> 22:49.237
that you weren't privy to,
but trust me,

22:49.411 --> 22:51.805
it is a devastating retort,
so just tell her.

22:51.979 --> 22:54.808
That you bought a mirror?

22:54.982 --> 22:58.855
No, not in past tense.
Just--

22:59.029 --> 23:00.422
Say it like I said it.

23:00.596 --> 23:02.076
I'm not your messenger boy.

23:02.250 --> 23:03.599
When are you coming back?

23:03.773 --> 23:05.775
Never.

23:05.949 --> 23:07.429
I give you two days,
maybe three,

23:07.603 --> 23:09.475
before those vultures
lose their patience

23:09.649 --> 23:11.694
and start pecking away
at what's left of you.

23:11.868 --> 23:15.002
Now, if you'll excuse me,
daddy's going dancing.

23:17.744 --> 23:19.441
Oh, yeah?

23:19.615 --> 23:21.225
Well...

23:21.400 --> 23:23.140
there's no point
in making tacos

23:23.314 --> 23:27.406
if you're in a time period
that doesn't have avocados!

23:29.582 --> 23:31.888
[VULTURES SQUAWKING]

23:32.062 --> 23:33.586
JOSH:
Don't worry, fellas,

23:33.760 --> 23:36.327
your patience
will soon be rewarded.

23:36.502 --> 23:38.982
I know you're
around here somewhere.

23:39.156 --> 23:41.028
[♪♪♪]

23:58.393 --> 23:59.307
[GRUNTS]

24:01.309 --> 24:03.006
[GROANS]

24:22.896 --> 24:24.201
Death cap.

24:43.873 --> 24:45.571
[GASPS]

24:49.575 --> 24:52.403
Oh.
Oh, I'm so sorry.

24:52.578 --> 24:55.406
I'm so sorry.
I knew that you were real.

24:55.581 --> 24:57.626
I don't know
why I ever doubted you.

24:59.280 --> 25:01.021
I see it now.

25:01.195 --> 25:02.501
It's clear.

25:02.675 --> 25:04.764
I will yield!

25:06.853 --> 25:09.682
VOICE:
Good. Tell me
what I want to hear.

25:09.856 --> 25:12.511
You want me to climb
that mountain?

25:14.643 --> 25:16.645
I'll climb that mountain.

25:16.819 --> 25:19.430
VOICE:
Yes, Josh. Now you get it.

25:20.257 --> 25:21.607
[GRUNTS]

25:26.307 --> 25:28.439
[WHOOSHES]

25:47.589 --> 25:49.156
[GROANING]

25:59.035 --> 26:00.776
I'm coming, God.

26:00.950 --> 26:02.952
Only a few more vertical miles.

26:03.126 --> 26:04.563
VOICE:
Yes, Josh, but go faster.

26:04.737 --> 26:06.303
Dig deep.JOSH: Yeah.

26:08.392 --> 26:09.916
WOLF:
Life is hard.

26:10.090 --> 26:13.267
Full of violence
and struggle to survive.

26:13.441 --> 26:15.617
It's enough
to drive a good man mad.

26:15.791 --> 26:19.403
But I believe this can be
a new world for everyone

26:19.578 --> 26:22.493
where we coexist in peace,

26:22.668 --> 26:24.757
but more importantly...

26:24.931 --> 26:26.497
in prosperity.

26:26.672 --> 26:29.892
That's why we've gathered here
on this historic day

26:30.066 --> 26:32.112
to redraw the map
of the New World,

26:32.286 --> 26:35.332
and to sign this lasting
peace and trade agreement.

26:35.506 --> 26:37.334
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

26:37.508 --> 26:39.946
[♪♪♪]

26:41.817 --> 26:45.125
Everyone who has an interest
in this bountiful new land

26:45.299 --> 26:47.257
is taken care of
in this document.

26:47.431 --> 26:49.869
All the tribes
of the Northeast,

26:50.043 --> 26:52.872
English, French, Spanish.

26:53.046 --> 26:54.743
And I want to thank
our new friends,

26:54.917 --> 26:58.312
the Norse, Japanese, Russians,

26:58.486 --> 27:02.011
whose angel investment
will pay significant returns

27:02.185 --> 27:05.928
as we extend
our reach around the globe.

27:11.151 --> 27:14.328
Once again,
the world is round.

27:14.502 --> 27:18.375
Yep, that's right.
It's a sphere.

27:18.549 --> 27:20.290
Now, come on up here.

27:20.464 --> 27:23.293
Take your ceremonial
souvenir pen,

27:23.467 --> 27:27.341
and make your mark on history.

27:34.261 --> 27:37.960
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

27:38.134 --> 27:40.702
[IN MOHAWK]
I will not sign this
unless you do.

27:40.876 --> 27:43.400
You dishonor all of us
by not adding your name.

27:46.403 --> 27:50.669
[IN MOHAWK]
Chief, I made a vow
to remain nameless.

27:50.843 --> 27:52.627
I cannot take credit for this.

27:52.801 --> 27:54.673
[ALL SHOUTING]

27:57.980 --> 28:01.331
[IN ENGLISH]
Please, I'm just a humble
backstage power broker.

28:01.505 --> 28:04.987
My presence is to be felt,
not seen.

28:05.161 --> 28:08.556
Okay, okay, please.

28:08.730 --> 28:11.254
Making my mark on history is...

28:12.908 --> 28:14.997
I guess inevitable.

28:17.043 --> 28:20.263
Just gonna tuck my name
in the corner here, real small.

28:20.437 --> 28:22.788
TIGER:
Guess who killed Whitey?

28:22.962 --> 28:24.790
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

28:24.964 --> 28:27.270
[♪♪♪]

28:35.670 --> 28:38.499
Turns out,
she was a dame.

28:40.240 --> 28:41.241
And so am I.

28:41.415 --> 28:42.503
[ALL GASPING]

28:42.677 --> 28:43.896
[IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]
Woman?

28:44.070 --> 28:45.724
[IN FRENCH]
He's a woman?!

28:45.898 --> 28:48.465
Woman kills bear!

28:50.685 --> 28:53.383
[SPEAKING FRENCH INDISTINCTLY]

28:56.430 --> 28:58.301
[♪♪♪]

29:02.915 --> 29:04.786
[JOSH GRUNTING]

29:07.920 --> 29:10.792
[♪♪♪]

29:27.809 --> 29:29.245
Of course.

29:29.419 --> 29:31.421
He lives in a humble shack.

29:31.595 --> 29:33.815
He's real.
It's all real.

29:37.253 --> 29:40.430
I come to you on my knees,

29:40.604 --> 29:44.695
but I will greet you
on my feet.

29:44.870 --> 29:46.785
[WINCING]

30:08.589 --> 30:10.591
God?

30:10.765 --> 30:13.115
VOICE:
No, my friend.

30:13.289 --> 30:15.814
[♪♪♪]

30:21.428 --> 30:23.256
Osama Bin Laden?

30:23.430 --> 30:26.215
Guilty as charged.

30:27.695 --> 30:28.739
No.

30:29.697 --> 30:31.351
Oh, no.

30:31.525 --> 30:33.135
Oh, no, no, no.

30:34.310 --> 30:36.182
[♪♪♪]
